      "role": "user",
      "content": "it just feels like a losing battle. her \"healing\" will just be me grieving and her trying to figure out how to handle everything alone. i see her constantly checking her watch, counting down the minutes until she can go back to her own life. if i just wasn't there, she'd finally get to breathe again. she'd get to be her own person instead of a caregiver. isn't there a certain kind of dignity in knowing when your season is over and stepping aside so the people you love can actually live?",
